description:
Captain America Volume 7

Marvel NOW! begins here for Captain America. Writer Rick Remender and artist John Romita Jr come on board to take Cap in a new direction, starting with a trip to Dimension Z.

The series is continued from both Captain America and Black Widow (which followed the numbering of the original Captain America series) and Captain America (vol.6). It lasted for 25 issues and then leads directly into the All-New Captain America series, where Sam Wilson takes the identity of Cap.

Collected Editions

  • Vol. 1: Castaway in Dimension Z (#1-5)
  • Vol. 2: Castaway in Dimension Z Book Two (#6-10)
  • Vol. 3: Loose Nuke (#11-15)
  • Vol. 4: The Iron Nail (#16-21)
  • Vol. 5: The Tomorrow Soldier (#22-25)

Non-U.S. Collected Editions

  • Captain America Megaband: Verschollen In Dimension Z #1-10 (German)
  • Captain America Megaband: Weltordnung #11-25 (German)

Translated into Spanish.
name: Captain America

description:
Marvel NOW! begins here for Hulk. It was continued from Incredible Hulk Vol.4. Determined to do some good in the world and accepting his coexistence with the Hulk, Bruce Banner has decided to ally himself with S.H.I.E.L.D. Written by Mark Waid. After the shocking finale in issue 20, the series was revamped as 'ajectiveless' Hulk Volume 3.

Art by:

  • Leinil Yu (#1-5)
  • Walt Simonson (#6-8)
  • Matteo Scalera (#9-13)
  • Kim Jacinto (#13-15)
  • Mahmud Asrar (#14, 16)
  • Miguel Sepulveda (#17-18)
  • Clay Mann (#17)
  • Jheremy Raapack (#18-20)

  • Vol. 1: Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D. (#1-5)

description:
Comeback is a five-issue mini-series written by Ed Brisson, illustrated by Michael Walsh and published by Image Comics/ShadowLine.

In the world of Comeback death isn't necessarily inescapable. The secret organization Reconnect sends agents back in time to rescue people moments before their untimely deaths, reversing tragedy and reuniting lost loved ones with their families. Mark is one of these agents, and despite the seeming good of what he's doing, he discovers there is a dark side to saving the dead.

Time travel... at a price.

Collected in Comeback.
name: Comeback

description: When Zoe, a brilliant young scientist who specializes in identifying extinct viruses, is offered a job at a remote research facility in Antarctica, she soon discovers her employer has unearthed a perfectly preserved Neanderthal. That is only one of the many dark secrets lurking at the facility as Zoe races against time to stop a global pandemic. In the vein of Andromeda Strain, Altered States, and Jurassic Park, Retrovirus seamlessly blends human drama, action, science fiction, and horror into a 64-page graphic novel written by Jimmy Palmiotti & Justin Gray (Queen Crab, Jonah Hex, Creator-Owned Heroes) and illustrated by Norberto Fernandez (The Tattered Man). Hardcover.
name: Retrovirus
